<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98205846028491></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98205846028491><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98205846028491>Soloing from 20-22 in 10 hours</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98205846028491#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Feb 13th 5:01 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I went from level 20 to 22 and made about 250pp in about ten hours of play.<br><br>Here's what I did:<br><br>As soon as I turned 20, I went to Ocean of Tears to buy my new spells. I bought them all. I summoned an earth pet and made sure he conned black to me and gave him a staff of warding. I bound myself on the Sisters Island and swam to the gargoyle island.<br><br>I parked my pet at the very edge of the island, out of the way of wandering skeles and gargoyles. The pet never left this spot. I buffed him with Burnout, and with Shield of Fire when I was ready to pull a gargoyle. I blasted the lvl 18-20 gargoyles with my level 20 dd spell once, ran back to my pet, then blasted again with either the lvl 20 or the lvl 16 dd, then just joined in the melee. I got it to a science where after every fight I had about 80% health and 70% mana, and my pet would have between 65-85% health, depending on the level of the gargoyle. It'd only take a minute or two for everything to regenerate to 100%.<br><br>Several times I pulled two gargoyles by accident. No problem. Just realize that you shouldn't try to beat them both. You'd probably die. Let your earth pet distract them -- meanwhile, gate away to the sister island. I don't know if they'd come after you from that far away, but I didn't take any chances. I just camped and entered again. Whatever you do, don't try to run away from gargoyles by swimming. They'll chase you into the water, and if you die in there, it can be a real pain in the neck.<br><br>Several hours later, I had killed about a hundred gargoyles and looted 30 gargoyle eyes. And I was suddenly level 22! :-)<br><br>Elviss<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
